      "rationale": "A simulation plan (SP-001 rev B) documents all boundary conditions, contact definitions, material assignments, and load application procedures. An independent reviewer (not the analyst) verified the setup against the plan before any results were extracted. No use errors identified during review. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form assumptions (linear elastic titanium alloy, frictionless screw-rod contact, rigid UHMWPE blocks) justified by sensitivity analysis showing <5% QoI sensitivity to friction coefficient over range 0.0–0.3.",
      "rationale": "Titanium alloy Ti-6Al-4V modeled as linear elastic (E=114 GPa, v=0.34) consistent with sub-yield loading regime confirmed by strain gauge data. Contact friction sensitivity: varying mu from 0.0 to 0.3 changes stiffness QoI by 2.1%, yield force by 3.4%. UHMWPE block rigidity assumption validated against block deformation measurements (<0.05 mm). Gradation 3 achieved: documented sensitivity analysis supporting model form choices."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometry inputs derived from lot-specific coupon testing and CMM measurements; input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo (N=1000) to establish 95% prediction interval on QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V elastic modulus measured from 5 tensile coupons from the same material lot (mean 113.8 GPa, CV 0.9%). Screw and rod geometry digitized by CMM for each of the 11 constructs. Monte Carlo propagation (N=1000) of material and geometry uncertainty yields 95% PI on stiffness of ±3.2%. Gradation 3 achieved: lot-specific inputs with formal uncertainty propagation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 test constructs from production lots; constructs represent the intended device population; traceability of each specimen to lot and dimensional records maintained.",
      "rationale": "Eleven (N=11) non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories. All constructs manufactured from the same production lot with full dimensional traceability. Sample size exceeds the minimum required for the chosen statistical acceptance metric (E/uval). Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios including at least two load levels or two construct configurations.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 standardized compression-bending configuration (35 mm offset, 10 mm/min crosshead speed, ambient temperature). Only one test condition was evaluated; no variation in offset distance, loading rate, or temperature was explored. This limits generalizability but is consistent with the COU scope. Achieves Gradation 2 only; required Gradation 3. This factor is below the required level and is documented as a known gap in the credibility assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions) demonstrably equivalent to test specimen conditions; equivalency documented for each of the 11 constructs.",
      "rationale": "CMM measurements of each test specimen were used to parameterize the corresponding FEA model instance. Material properties derived from same-lot coupon tests. Boundary conditions replicate the ASTM F1717 fixture geometry as verified by fixture drawings. Per-construct equivalency table documented in simulation plan appendix. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation metric E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs; percent difference between FEA ensemble mean and experimental mean < 10% for all QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Stiffness: E/uval = 0.84, mean difference 3.1%. Yield force: E/uval = 1.12, mean difference 4.7%. Force at 40 mm: E/uval = 0.97, mean difference 2.9%. All three QoIs satisfy both acceptance criteria. Validation metric computed per ASME V&V 40 Section 5.3.3 using combined simulation and experimental uncertainty. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
