    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation level. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is accepted on the basis that the ASTM F1717 single-condition protocol is the regulatory standard for this device class and the COU is explicitly scoped to that protocol. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-specified acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; mean difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is accepted as credible for the stated COU.",
